Yesterday, Waterville Central School District was informed that the New York State Department of Health did not receive the district's Reopening Plan.

As required by the New York State Education Department, Waterville Central School District's Reopening Plan was publicly available to students and parents and submitted to the New York State Education Department on Friday, July 31. The New York State Department of Health confirmed their receipt of the Reopening Plan on Monday, August 10.

The plan continues to be available at:
http://ow.ly/QrF350AWVHV

MPS Positivity Project: Need some good news? Here's an update on our MPS adopted koala, Paul. "Paul has surprised us! His battle back to health has concerned us greatly at times. He's such a little battler! Paul's treatment plan continues, but for now he is eating as much as any young koala could...filling out that thin body of his. Thank you to all of you who sponsor and ask after him. We appreciate your support!"
#koalahospital

post_text:
MPS Positivity Project: This week, our #P2PartnerSchools will focus on the character strength of creativity. Creative people are able to look at the world in original ways. They are open to new experiences, and have an imaginative and independent thought process. They are able to generate lots of different ideas, and have the capacity to go after certain ideas they‚Äôve generated with energy and enthusiasm. Creativity is a process that takes courage. Anytime you‚Äôre putting your original ideas into the world, you risk being criticized or even ostracized.

Positive psychology breaks creativity into two components. First, he/she must produce original ideas or behaviors. Second, the original idea or behavior must make a positive contribution to that person‚Äôs life or others lives. There are big acts of creativity, exemplified by great artists and scientists. And, there are everyday acts of creativity, such as how people create solutions to deal with problems at work or at home.

#character #creativity #otherpeoplemattermindset

post_text:
MPS Partner Schools: This week, our #P2PartnerSchools will discuss the character strength of perseverance. The concept of perseverance can most often be found in one‚Äôs active pursuit in overcoming obstacles. Perseverance is a characteristic that identifies an individual‚Äôs ability to spend long periods of time devoted to a single goal or set of goals. Those who persevere are able to set goals for themselves and then take active, calculated steps toward those goals. People demonstrating high levels of perseverance are able to handle significant, sometimes repeated, setbacks in pursuit of goals.

#character #perseverance #otherpeoplematter

post_text:
From Miss Linder, MPS School Librarian!!!

Check out some of the creative readers taking part in the reading challenge through the MPS Library the past few weeks! Aren't they all awesome?

Students have the opportunity to email a new reading challenge photo each week to Miss Linder, for a chance to win a Barnes & Noble gift card! I am so grateful the MPS PTA is helping out too, which is enabling more students to win!

You have a couple more days to get your photos in by Friday this week, super readers! Keep smiling and keep reading,

I'm so proud of you all!

-Miss Linder

of the United States of America

Child care placement is available to personnel who provide essential services, supplies, or support during this unprecedented time. For a full list of personnel who may qualify, please visit our website at http://ow.ly/zpld50yWSfs.

Essential personnel can call the Oneida-Herkimer-Madison Child Care Resource Center at 315-223-7850 extension 222 or email earlycareandlearning@cornell.edu for information on childcare
placement.

The Child Care Resource Center will continue to evaluate and adjust plans as necessary to best meet the childcare needs of essential personnel.

Thank you to all essential personnel who continue to protect and support our community.

Please be safe, and whenever possible, stay at home.
